SIMPLE: storied
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Storied
<hw>Sto"ried</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Story</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Told in a story.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a history; interesting from the stories which
pertain to it; venerable from the associations of the past.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some greedy minion, or imperious wife,⟦br⟧
The trophied arches, <qex>storied</qex> halls, invade.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Can <qex>storied</qex> urn, or animated bust,⟦br⟧
Back to its mansion call the fleeting breath?</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having (such or so many) stories; -- chiefly in
composition; <as>as, a two-<ex>storied</ex> house</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Storier</ent>⟦br⟧
